  "text": "We then decided to test whether APPL1 is involved in synaptic plasticity. APPL1 interacts with Rab5 and participates in endocytic signaling (Miaczynska et al., 2004; [CITATION_1] . We have previously shown that Rab5-driven endocytosis mediates the removal of AMPARs from synapses during NMDAR-dependent LTD [CITATION_2] . Therefore, we first tested whether APPL1 is required for this form of LTD. Surprisingly, both uninfected and shAPPL1-infected neurons displayed strong NMDAR-dependent LTD (Fig. 3A,B) . Therefore, we conclude that the endocytic functions of APPL1 are not required for AMPAR synaptic removal during NMDAR-dependent LTD.",
